  "2026-07-14T20:17:42.518Z",codex-root,"Linked-test diagnostic: the first acceptance run passed 102 init/completion tests but the contract snapshot check failed only because pm test correctly sandboxed PM_PATH with zero tracker items/extensions, while contracts:check intentionally snapshots the real project package surface. Direct pnpm contracts:check on the real tracker is current. Re-running the linked set with explicit tracker context records the intended package-aware acceptance evidence."
  "2026-07-14T20:19:50.622Z",codex-root,"Final evidence: canonical --id-prefix and --prefix alias work with flag-only, positional-only, normalized equivalent dual input, empty-input refusal, and deterministic conflict guidance. Bash/zsh/fish completions, runtime contracts, docs, direct registration forwarding, integration coverage, and packed installed-CLI temp-workspace proof pass. Linked acceptance rerun is green (102 init/completion tests plus current project contract snapshot). Full repository verification is 5,701 tests at literal 100/100/100/100 coverage."
  "2026-07-14T20:44:53.144Z",codex-root,"PR #563 round-1 review: accepted Greptile's path-like flagged-prefix finding and added init_id_prefix_path_like refusal with actionable positional/global-path guidance plus unit/integration coverage. Rejected the separate alias-drop claim: Commander, repository integration tests, and Greptile T-Rex all prove --prefix ops persists ops-. All four inline bot comments were reacted to and answered in their real threads. Post-fix full suite remains 5,701 tests with 36,850/36,850 statements, 26,465/26,465 branches, 7,438/7,438 functions, and 35,965/35,965 lines."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T20:19:51.329Z",codex-root,"Commander stores the canonical property from the long flag declaration, so --prefix, --id-prefix <value> forwards through options.idPrefix; resolving positional and flag forms in one normalizer keeps compatibility and conflict behavior deterministic."
